512/* Most COFF variants have no way to record the alignment of a
513 section. This struct is used to set a specific alignment based on
514 the name of the section. */
515
516struct coff_section_alignment_entry
517{
518 /* The section name. */
519 const char *name;
520
521 /* This is either (unsigned int) -1, indicating that the section
522 name must match exactly, or it is the number of letters which
523 must match at the start of the name. */
524 unsigned int comparison_length;
525
526 /* These macros may be used to fill in the first two fields in a
527 structure initialization. */
528#define COFF_SECTION_NAME_EXACT_MATCH(name) (name), ((unsigned int) -1)
529#define COFF_SECTION_NAME_PARTIAL_MATCH(name) (name), (sizeof (name) - 1)
530
531 /* Only use this entry if the default section alignment for this
532 target is at least that much (as a power of two). If this field
533 is COFF_ALIGNMENT_FIELD_EMPTY, it should be ignored. */
534 unsigned int default_alignment_min;
535
536 /* Only use this entry if the default section alignment for this
537 target is no greater than this (as a power of two). If this
538 field is COFF_ALIGNMENT_FIELD_EMPTY, it should be ignored. */
539 unsigned int default_alignment_max;
540
541#define COFF_ALIGNMENT_FIELD_EMPTY ((unsigned int) -1)
542
543 /* The desired alignment for this section (as a power of two). */
544 unsigned int alignment_power;
545};

620typedef struct coff_ptr_struct
621{
622 /* Remembers the offset from the first symbol in the file for
623 this symbol. Generated by coff_renumber_symbols. */
624 unsigned int offset;
625
626 /* Should the value of this symbol be renumbered. Used for
627 XCOFF C_BSTAT symbols. Set by coff_slurp_symbol_table. */
628 unsigned int fix_value : 1;
629
630 /* Should the tag field of this symbol be renumbered.
631 Created by coff_pointerize_aux. */
632 unsigned int fix_tag : 1;
633
634 /* Should the endidx field of this symbol be renumbered.
635 Created by coff_pointerize_aux. */
636 unsigned int fix_end : 1;
637
638 /* Should the x_csect.x_scnlen field be renumbered.
639 Created by coff_pointerize_aux. */
640 unsigned int fix_scnlen : 1;
641
642 /* Fix up an XCOFF C_BINCL/C_EINCL symbol. The value is the
643 index into the line number entries. Set by coff_slurp_symbol_table. */
644 unsigned int fix_line : 1;
645
646 /* The container for the symbol structure as read and translated
647 from the file. */
648 union
649 {
650 union internal_auxent auxent;
651 struct internal_syment syment;
652 } u;
653
654 /* Selector for the union above. */
655 bfd_boolean is_sym;
656} combined_entry_type;

659/* Each canonical asymbol really looks like this: */
660
661typedef struct coff_symbol_struct
662{
663 /* The actual symbol which the rest of BFD works with */
664 asymbol symbol;
665
666 /* A pointer to the hidden information for this symbol */
667 combined_entry_type *native;
668
669 /* A pointer to the linenumber information for this symbol */
670 struct lineno_cache_entry *lineno;
671
672 /* Have the line numbers been relocated yet ? */
673 bfd_boolean done_lineno;
674} coff_symbol_type;
675/* COFF symbol classifications. */
676
677enum coff_symbol_classification
678{
679 /* Global symbol. */
680 COFF_SYMBOL_GLOBAL,
681 /* Common symbol. */
682 COFF_SYMBOL_COMMON,
683 /* Undefined symbol. */
684 COFF_SYMBOL_UNDEFINED,
685 /* Local symbol. */
686 COFF_SYMBOL_LOCAL,
687 /* PE section symbol. */
688 COFF_SYMBOL_PE_SECTION
689};
